Help on skill:     Ancestral call
Usage duration:    random
Fatigue:           minimal
Skill type:        special
Affecting stat(s): constitution, skill percent and inner strength
The blood of ancient warriors flows in your veins. Their spirits walk beside
you, watching over their descendants with pride. Through deep communion with
these ancestral souls, you can call upon their wisdom and strength to guide
your hand in battle.
When you invoke this ancient rite, the spirits of your forebears manifest
around you - not as ghosts, but as echoes of will and power that merge with
your own. Their battle-hardened instincts guide your strikes with supernatural
precision and speed.
This is the essence of the Savage path - you do not fight alone. You carry
the strength of generations, and when you call, they answer.
Using this skill costs three points of fury.
---------------------------------------------------
Help on skill:  Ancestral leap
Usage duration: random
Fatigue:        low
Skill type:     misc
An ancient primal technique passed down through countless generations
of barbarian warriors. By calling upon ancestral spirits and tapping
into the primal bonds that connect all barbarians to sacred places,
a warrior can leap through the spirit realm itself, emerging at
locations infused with tribal power.
The technique requires immense physical and spiritual energy, as the
warrior must forcefully tear open a path through the veil between
worlds. Only places deeply bound to barbarian heritage - guild halls,
ancient battlegrounds, ritual sites - resonate strongly enough to
serve as anchors for this journey.
Skilled warriors can also sense the spiritual echoes of other living
souls, allowing them to tear through reality itself to reach distant
allies or enemies. The spirits care not for distance - only that the
barbarian's will is strong enough to breach the boundaries between
here and there.
Usage: use ancestral leap at <destination>
use ancestral leap at list  (to see available destinations)
