Help on skill:     Crimson charge
Usage duration:    random
Fatigue:           very low
Skill type:        attack
Affecting stat(s): strength, constitution, attack, anatomy, spot weakness and
skill percent
The blood calls. Not metaphorically, not symbolically - your own blood,
ancient and knowing, demands to be spilled. The civilized recoil from
self-inflicted wounds, calling it madness. They understand nothing of
power written in scars, of strength purchased with sacrifice.
You tear open old wounds or carve new ones, letting your blood flow free.
As crimson streams down your body, something awakens - the blood of every
ancestor who fell in battle, every warrior whose line led to you. Their
fury mingles with yours, their strength becomes yours. Pain becomes fuel.
When you charge, you are no longer alone. Unseen hands guide your weapon.
Ancient rage amplifies your fury. The blood-price paid transforms you into
something more than mortal, and when you crash into your enemy trailing
crimson, they face not just you, but the weight of every bloodline warrior
who demands vengeance through your hands.
Blood demands blood. The ancestors accept no other currency.
Using this skill generates two points of fury.
---------------------------------------------------
Help on skill:     Danger sense
Usage duration:    automatic
Skill type:        defensive
Affecting stat(s): strength and fury level
Death teaches quickly. Survive enough battles and something primal awakens
within: not thought, not technique, but pure predatory awareness. The kind
of instinct that keeps apex predators alive in their brutal world.
Where trained warriors analyze and calculate, the barbarian simply knows.
The shift in air pressure before a blade falls. The tensing of muscle
before a spell unleashes. The body moves before the mind registers the
threat, erupting away from danger with the explosive violence of a cornered
beast.
Others call it luck. Those who possess it know better. This is what happens
when fury and survival instinct m
erge into something beyond mere skill. When
one has danced with death so often that its approach is recognized by scent
alone.
And when death's strike misses? That's when the predator strikes back.
---------------------------------------------------
Help on skill:     Defiant roar
Usage duration:    0 round
Skill type:        passive
Affecting stat(s): constitution, fury level, stupor and skill percent
There are moments when the fury burning in barbarian veins refuses to be
contained, even when the body is battered and stunned. Berserker rage does
not bow to pain or exhaustion - it feeds on them. When lesser warriors
would fall helpless, barbarian fury erupts in a defiant roar that shatters
whatever forces seek to bind.
This primal surge of adrenaline breaks the stunned free and momentarily
dulls pain, allowing the fight to continue when others would fall.
