Help on skill:     Primal roar
Usage duration:    random
Fatigue:           very low
Skill type:        attack
Affecting stat(s): strength, anatomy, attack, spot weakness, constitution and
skill percent
Civilized armies march in silence, maintaining discipline and formation.
They believe noise weakens strategy. Fools. The primal tribes know what
those orderly ranks have forgotten: sound itself i s a weapon. Not words,
not commands - raw, inhuman, bone-shaking fury given voice.
Your roar is not merely loud. It carries physical force, reverberating
through enemy bodies like a shockwave. Ears ring. Vision blurs. The
confident warrior who stood ready a heartbeat ago now staggers, their
certainty shattered by the primal reminder that they are prey, and you
are predator.
Where the enemy hears terror, your allies hear something else: the call
to war. The sound that says the hunt has begun. Their own fury rises to
match yours.
The roar is older than language, more honest than steel.
Using this skill generates two points of fury.
---------------------------------------------------
Help on skill:     Reckless strike
Usage duration:    random
Fatigue:           low
Skill type:        attack
Affecting stat(s): strength, constitution, attack, anatomy, spot weakness,
critical and skill percent
Combat instructors teach balance. Maintain your guard. Never overcommit.
Protect yourself while attacking. The barbarian rejects this philosophy
entirely. There are moments when caution is cowardice, when defense is
delay, when the only path forward is through absolute, reckless violence.
Throw aside every lesson about protection. Abandon guard. Overextend.
Commit everything, body, weapon, fury itself, into one devastating strike
delivered with such overwhelming force that the enemy's defense becomes
meaningless. Let them see the opening you create. Let them understand what's
coming. It changes nothing.
This is not technique or strategy. This is the moment when you decide that
killing your enemy matters more than your own safety, and you make that
decision with steel and fury. Either they fall or you do.
Civilized warriors fight to survive. The barbarian fights to kill.
Using this skill generates two points of fury.
---------------------------------------------------
Help on skill:     Relentless
Usage duration:    automatic
Skill type:        passive
Affecting stat(s): constitution, stamina and skill percent
The barbarian way is one of endless endurance. Where civilized warriors
tire and falter, the barbarian presses on. Where others must rest and
recover, the hunt continues. This is not mere stubbornness - it is a
fundamental truth of existence. Pain is temporary, exhaustion is weakness,
and surrender is death.
The body forged through countless trials becomes an instrument of relentless
warfare. Recovery from exertion comes faster than normal warriors, and
actions frequently cost less stamina. The longer a battle extends, the more
the advantage grows as weaker opponents exhaust themselves while the
barbarian presses on with unyielding determination.
