Help on skill:     Savage charge
Usage duration:    random
Fatigue:           very low
Skill type:        attack
Affecting stat(s): strength, constitution, attack, anatomy, spot weakness and
skill percent
Civilized warriors respect distance. They maneuver cautiously, close gaps
with measured steps, maintain defensive posture while advancing. This is
what cowards call tactics. The savage knows better: distance is an illusion
that exists only for those too weak to shatter it.
Fury demands blood now. Not after careful positioning. Not when the tactical
situation favors it. Now. You explode forward with the momentum of an
avalanche, closing impossible gaps in heartbeats, weapon raised, the roar
of your charge announcing what your enemy already knows: running is futile.
The impact when you arrive is not combat, it is collision. They prepared
to fight, but you don't fight at distance. You arrive like a force of
nature and obliterate whatever stands before you. By the time they register
you've moved, your weapon has already found them.
Distance is a courtesy. The savage extends no courtesies.
Using this skill generates two points of fury.
